The paper deals with image retrieval and classification using deep hashing methods, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) applications. Therefore, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes an unsupervised learning framework, which involves loss functions and optimization techniques, indicating that it may fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on standard datasets, which suggests that it may belong to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM).
